office of accessible education accommodation letters student affairs office of accessible education students faculty & teaching staff about the oae schwab learning center resources & faqs stanford university student affairs all stanford search submit accommodation letters office of accessible education accommodation letters are provided to students in order to communicate the academic adjustments appropriate based on the student's disability accommodations are determined on an individualized basis and should in no way compromise the essential elements in the course after meeting with a disability advisor or a learning specialist you may request an accommodation letter accommodation letters will be delivered electronically to you via e mail you are responsible for passing this information along to the appropriate individual within your degree program eg faculty member associate dean advising coordinator etc the appropriate individual to inform about accommodations may be found from the accommodation process page the academic accommodations stated in the letter may need to be modified based on interactive discussions with faculty if the accommodations are believed to fundamentally alter the course when requesting exam accommodations it is necessary to submit the request for exam accommodations one week prior to the exam date up groups office of accessible education printer friendly version search oae search oae information location & hours disgo cart service jobs at the oae office of accessible education 563 salvatierra walk stanford california 94305 650 723 1066 voice 650 725 5301 fax im oaegetinfo provide feedback copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
